50+ Linux Command for Cloud Engineers
Cmd: ls
Full Form: List Segments  
Definition: This command is used to list files and directories within the current locations
working directory.
Example: ls -l  (This will list the files and directories along with their permissions, size, owner, group, and date and time of the last modification details)

Command: pwd
Full Form: Print Working Directory
Definition: It shows the full pathname of the current working directory.
Example: pwd -
Executing this command will output the full path to the current directory.
